Name: Acceptance rate
Description: This type holds information about the acceptance rate of schools, expressed as the percentage of students who applied that were actually admitted (e.g., a value between 0 - 100, where 100 means 100% meaning all students who applied were accepted.)

Properties.Name: Rate
Properties.Description: The percentage of people who applied in a given year that were actually admitted (i.e., a value between 0 and 100, where 100 means all students who applied were accepted).

Properties.Name: Year
Properties.Description: The beginning year of the academic year this data is valid for. E.g., for academic year 2011-2012, enter "2011".
